(Tried Biryanis)
Went to for Lunch while exploring options in South Goa. This place is good and gives real goan vibes. Well south Goa is neat and kind of peace. The restaurant is maintained good and with helpful staffs all orders are easy pesy. We tried below items
1. Chicken Biryani : 3.5/5
.   Rice : 3.5
.   Chicken : 4/5

2. Prawn Biryani :4/5
.   Rice : 4/5
.   Praws :4.5/5

Raita and salan : 3/5.

Good luck.

I personally loved this place. I visited this place so many times no matter whether itâ€™s breakfast, lunch or dinner.

I had very less hopes for dal khichdi in goa but this place made me realise how amazing their food is by proving to sell best dal khichdi in town.

I have tried their most of the dishes and everything is just delicious.

Go for anything you like here, I am pretty sure that will be really delicious.

Ate here twice once for dinner and once for breakfast. The dosa are very tasty. The main courses were ok. However both times one member of our group got diarrea. The first time about an hour later, the second time immediately after finishing the meal. The toilet is a bit on the dirty side, with lots of tiny flies all over the toilet.
